            "id": "4582590",
            "title": "AvalonBay, Equity Residential weigh megamerger - report",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">AvalonBay Communities (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AVB\" title=\"AvalonBay Communities, Inc.\">AVB</a></span>) and Equity Residential (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EQR\" title=\"Equity Residential\">EQR</a></span>) have held exploratory talks about merging two of the biggest apartment developers in the U.S., according to a media report on Thursday.</p>\n<p>AvalonBay (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AVB\" title=\"AvalonBay Communities, Inc.\">AVB</a>) stock rose 2.0%, and Equity Residential (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EQR\" title=\"Equity Residential\">EQR</a>) stock gained 1.0% in premarket trading.</p>\n<p>The deliberations are preliminary, and there's no guarantee they will result in a transaction, Bloomberg <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-29/top-us-apartment-owners-avalonbay-eqr-said-to-discuss-combining?srnd=homepage-americas\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"reported\">reported</a>, citing people familiar with the matter.</p>\n<p>The combination of the two apartment REITs could dramatically reshape the sector. Each of the companies has a market cap of ~$25B, making them the biggest apartment REITs in the U.S. in terms of market value.</p>\n<p>As of March 31, 2026, AvalonBay (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AVB\" title=\"AvalonBay Communities, Inc.\">AVB</a>) held direct or indirect ownership of ~98.3K apartments, while Equity Residential (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EQR\" title=\"Equity Residential\">EQR</a>) owned ~85.2K apartment homes, the companies disclosed in their financial statements.</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
